# gitchat — Project Context

## What this is

A conversational interface for exploring a GitHub profile's contribution activity. All data is **mocked** — design quality and interaction are the focus, not API integration. The data layer is separated cleanly so it can be swapped for real APIs later.

## Design direction

**"Editorial + Data Sculpture"** — magazine-spread aesthetic, not a typical SaaS dashboard. Avoid looking like a GitHub/Linear/Vercel clone.

Key principles:
- Large typography, generous whitespace, intentional asymmetry
- Two-register layout: editorial side (profile, heatmap, repos) + marginalia column (conversation)
- The heatmap is a **visual centerpiece**, not a sidebar widget
- Narration has **two tones**: heatmap clicks are playful/witty, repo clicks are formal/informative

## Tech stack

| Tool | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| React 19 + TypeScript | UI framework |
| Vite | Build tool |
| SCSS Modules + design tokens | Styling (`src/styles/tokens/`) |
| Zustand | State management (chat store, layout store) |
| Framer Motion | Animations and layout transitions |
| ESLint 9 (flat config) + Prettier | Lint and format |

## Project structure

```
src/
  components/       # Feature components, each in its own folder
    Profile/        # Profile.tsx + Profile.module.scss + index.ts
    Heatmap/
    RepoStack/
    Conversation/
  data/             # Mock data generators (contributions, profile, repos)
  lib/              # Business logic (store, stats engine, responses, commentary)
  styles/           # Global styles and design tokens
    tokens/         # _colors.scss, _typography.scss, _spacing.scss
  types/            # Shared TypeScript interfaces
```

## Node version

Pinned in `.nvmrc` — always run `nvm use` first.

## Conventions at a glance

- 2-space indent, single quotes, semicolons, trailing commas (Prettier enforced)
- `printWidth: 100`; JSX uses double quotes
- Named exports for components; `App` uses default export
- One component per folder with colocated SCSS module and barrel `index.ts`
- Shared animation easing: `[0.22, 1, 0.36, 1]` across all components
- `localStorage` used for persisting chat panel side preference
- `prefers-reduced-motion` respected globally in `global.scss`
